content.text:
To overload functions, they must have the same name but different parameter lists. The syntax is:
return_type function_name(parameter_list_1) {
  // code block
}
return_type function_name(parameter_list_2) {
  // code block
}
- **return_type**: The type of value returned (can differ).
- **function_name**: The same name for all overloaded functions.
- **parameter_list**: Must differ in number or type of parameters.
Different return types alone are not sufficient for overloading; the parameter list must differ.

